snippet.textDisplay: As a quail farmer, I’d advise that in the future, it’s okay to help them hatch when they’ve progressed that far. They can become so exhausted and weak that they will die if they are stuck like that one at the end was. If the chick begins to zip the egg but doesn’t emerge, it’s ideal to leave it, but when it’s basically hatched with just a tiny setback, it’s best to help him a bit!!
